abstract: >
  CQ4OE is a benchmark for the systematic and reproducible evaluation of
  LLM-based ontology generation from competency questions. For each of six
  source ontologies, CQ4OE provides a CQ-driven gold OWL ontology with
  explicit provenance linking each competency question to the classes,
  properties, and axioms required to answer it. From this resource we derive
  two complementary evaluation tasks. CQ2Term supports term-level evaluation
  of CQ-specific class and property prediction over 99 CQs. CQ2Onto supports
  full-ontology evaluation over 118 CQs, including hierarchy, property
  modeling, and axiom-level structure.
